cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on congestion control in wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a congestion control algorithm based on physical-layer bandwidth measurements, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of wireless network congestion on end-to-end network flows, which can affect multimedia applications. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to wireless networks and congestion control. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper implements a proof-of-concept prototype of the PBE measurement module on software-defined radios, which involves hardware architecture concepts.
